<!-- ============ SLIDE 2 : THE STORY, PT 1 ============ -->
<section class="slide" data-title="The Journey">
  <div class="kicker">The story behind the song · Part 1</div>
  <h2>The Journey</h2>
  <p>From the green hills of Ireland to the high ridges of Appalachia, my family carried the old blood westward. Through Arkansas dust, across Oklahoma wind, into the bold red heart of Texas, they marched with hardship on their backs and history in their bones.</p>
  <p>Each generation bore its share of sorrow, each land left its mark, and yet the family tree kept growing — strong, wild, and unbroken. What began in the Celtic roots of Ireland became the spirit of mountain folk and cowboys, a bloodline forged by suffering, strengthened by survival, and still moving west until it reached California.</p>
  <p class="pull">"From the old country to the new frontier,<br>our bloodline carried what the heart could bear."</p>
  <div class="note">
    <span class="tag">Presenter note</span>
    <p>Set the scene. This is the foundation of the song — the family migration saga that gives every word its weight.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ SLIDE 3 : THE STORY, PT 2 ============ -->
<section class="slide" data-title="The Legacy">
  <div class="kicker">The story behind the song · Part 2</div>
  <h2>The Legacy</h2>
  <p>At every stop along the way, life brought trials and tribulations — hunger, loss, hardship, and heartbreak — but those struggles only made the bloodline stronger. The stories passed down through the family became part of who we are: mountain folk, Irish cowboys, wanderers, survivors, and builders.</p>
  <p>That legacy eventually led all the way to California, where the journey continued, but the roots remained the same. This song is my way of honoring that evolution — the pain, the resilience, the faith, and the strength that came from the old country and grew into something bold and unbreakable in America.</p>
  <p>Songwriting had always been part of who I was, but telling this story felt bigger than me. AI tools became my assistants: helping me organize thoughts, sketch lyrics, refine melodies, and map out song structures without losing the emotional weight of the family history.</p>
  <p class="pull">"AI didn't replace my family's story; it helped me tell it.<br>It let me write again, honoring the bloodline that made me."</p>
  <p>This song is the result: a tribute to the generations who endured, who passed down their stories, and who made me who I am. Through tutorials like this, I want to show how AI-assisted songwriting can help anyone tell their family legacy — the pain, the resilience, and the fire that never died.</p>
  <p class="pull">"From Ireland to Appalachia, through dust and wind,<br>our bloodline carried on, and the song never ends."</p>
  <div class="note">
    <span class="tag">Presenter note</span>
    <p>This is where the story connects to the tutorial: AI as assistant, not replacement. Your story stays in charge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

