<!-- ============ THE LYRICS ============ -->
<section class="slide" data-title="The Lyrics">
  <div class="kicker">The finished product</div>
  <h2>"Too Far West" — The Lyrics</h2>
  <div class="lyrics">
    <div class="stanza"><h4>VERSE 1</h4><p>From Irish rain to Appalachian hills,<br>They carried songs and a stubborn will,<br>Built their lives where the cold winds crest,<br>But the road kept callin' them out west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza chorus"><h4>CHORUS</h4><p>He rode that line like a man possessed,<br>Chasin' dreams he never could catch,<br>Every mile just a wild unrest—<br>That cowboy went too far west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza"><h4>VERSE 2</h4><p>Through Choctaw land and Oklahoma dust,<br>He mixed his blood and he earned his trust,<br>Found him love but it wouldn't rest,<br>So he packed it up and he headed west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza chorus"><h4>CHORUS</h4><p>Yeah, he rode that line like a man possessed,<br>With a past behind and no time to rest,<br>Every town just another test—<br>That cowboy went too far west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza"><h4>VERSE 3</h4><p>Texas sun and the oilfield flame,<br>Raised another boy with a wanderin' name,<br>He said, "There's more past the sunset crest,"<br>And he kept that curse—goin' further west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza chorus"><h4>CHORUS</h4><p>Lord, he rode that line like a man possessed,<br>Never stayed long, never second-guessed,<br>Born to wander, forever unrest—<br>That cowboy went too far west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza"><h4>VERSE 4 (SLOW)</h4><p>California coast where the ocean ends,<br>No more road and no more bends,<br>He stood there still like a final test…<br>A cowboy man with no more west.</p></div>
    <div class="stanza chorus"><h4>FINAL CHORUS</h4><p>He rode that line like a man possessed,<br>All that runnin' laid down to rest,<br>Maybe he lost… or maybe he's blessed—<br>That cowboy went too far west.</p></div>
  </div>
  <div class="note">
    <span class="tag">Presenter note</span>
    <p>This is Phase 1 + 2 made real: the story (Ireland → California) mapped into verses and a repeating chorus. Point out the rhyme pairs — crest/west, possessed/unrest, dust/trust. That's the thesaurus method at work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ SLIDE 4 : PHASE 1 ============ -->
<section class="slide" data-title="Phase 1">
  <span class="phase-badge">Phase 1 · Foundation &amp; Storytelling</span>
  <h2>Pick your lane, write your heart</h2>
  <h3>1 · Select your genre &amp; taste profile</h3>
  <p>Identify the musical lane that resonates with your identity or taste.</p>
  <div class="chips"><span class="chip">Folk</span><span class="chip">Outlaw Country</span><span class="chip">Spaghetti Western</span><span class="chip">YOUR genre here</span></div>
  <h3>2 · Write the core story — the "heart" of the song</h3>
  <p>Draft a narrative prose block: a personal experience, a family legacy, or a fictional journey. Write freely — <strong>no rhyme, no structure, no rules yet.</strong></p>
  <div class="note">
    <span class="tag">Troy says</span>
    <p>"I write a story first. Whether it's my background, true story or fake story, my ethnic background and my story of my family I chose. And then I pick the style, and then I write a story."</p>
